    <div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
        <h4 class="header">Regional Status</h4>
        

        <ul class="text">
        
            <li><b>Central California Coast</b> (261Af, Ai-l). Stands generally exist on Montara Mountain in San Mateo Co. (CNDDB 2008) and at the San Francisco Presidio. Stands  of <i>Morella californica </i>are likely as far south as San Luis Obispo Co. based on plant collections (Jepson Flora Project 2021).</li>
        
            <li><b>Northern California Coast</b> (263Aa-b, Ad-e, Ag-l). Stands occur scattered along the North Coast from Marin Co. north to the Oregon border. At Point Reyes National Seashore they associate with stands of <i>Baccharis pilularis, Calamagrostis nutkaensis, </i>and <i>Carex obnupta, </i>alliances (Keeler-Wolf et al. 2003a). At Ring Mountain in Marin Co. they occur along intermittent streams adjacent to serpentine <i>Nassella pulchra </i>stands. Stands on the dunes west of Humboldt Bay mix with forests of <i>Picea sitchensis </i>and <i>Pinus contorta </i>ssp. <i>contorta.</i> Stands also exist in Mendocino Co., including Belinda Point Preserve (CNPS unpublished data 2020).</li>
        
            <li><b>Southern California Coast</b> (261Ba). Stands of <i>Morella californica </i>are likely, localized along marshes and creeks based on plant collections (Jepson Flora Project 2021).</li>
        
        </ul>
    </div>


    
	
<div class="allianceSection collapsable collapsed">
	 <h4 class="header">Management Considerations</h4>
	<div class="text"> Plants respond quickly to disturbance, including by basal sprouting and rhizomes, and they can stabilize soils and control erosion (Gonzalves and Darris 2016, Stevens and Darris 2000). Stands are often small, and individual plants grow in many coastal alliances. Seral relationships with other shrublands and wetlands dominated by <i>Carex obnupta, Salix lasiolepis, S. hookeriana, </i>and <i>Scirpus microcarpus </i>are complex and may have been influenced by past grazing, clearing, and in some cases fire.  Also, wind and salt spray effectively prune shrubs and trees found in the alliance, and <i>Morella </i>can form excellent hedges. </div>
</div>

    

    

